<HEADLINE>
`IT WAS LIKE A TOTO MOMENT'
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JEFF PRINCE 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARLINGTON, Texas _ Some pets had close calls, a few were still
missing, and at least one was found dead after Tuesday's tornado,
but most survived unscathed.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've only had a few calls for lost dogs; it's kind of
surprising,'' said Mike Pugliese, kennel manager at the Arlington
Humane Society.
