<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-30 02:03 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2012 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s BC-BKN-LAKERS-LADN-(SLAN     03-30 0655
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BRYANT'S 28 POINTS LEAD LAKERS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   VANCOUVER, B.C. _ The ever-streaking Lakers are piling up
victories behind power and grit more than quickness, but it was
their speed that was on display Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
   From zero to 60, in just 72 games.
</P>
<P>
   Before the last two days of March could even be crossed off the
wall calendar, the Lakers recorded their 60th win, with a 108-99
victory over the Vancouver Grizzlies at GM Place.
</P>
<P>
   The victory got them to that cherished plateau faster than any
team in franchise history but one _ the 1971-72 Lakers, who did it
in 71 games, and went on to win the championship.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're really happy to have 60 wins this fast,'' said Derek
Fisher. ``I mean, we've won 60 games before, but it seems we've had
to throw in everything and the kitchen sink to get to that point.
And this season it really seems, even though we've really worked
hard, that it came rather easy.''
</P>
<P>
   Never easier than this win, as the Lakers had a 14-point lead by
halftime and never looked back as they swept the season series from
the lowly Grizzlies.
</P>
<P>
   In the more pressing foot race, the Lakers are close to lapping
the field _ they reduced their magic number for clinching top seed
in the West to four. Any combination of Lakers wins and Portland
losses adding up to four will give the Lakers the prized home-court
advantage throughout the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers also won their seventh in a row and their 26th in
their past 27 games.
</P>
<P>
   And they did it without one member of their scoring trio, as
Glen Rice stayed home with a stomach virus. But Kobe Bryant's 28
points led six Lakers in double figures, and they overcame one of
their less-memorable defensive showings of the season.
</P>
<P>
   Behind 30 points from Shareef Abdur-Rahim, the Grizzlies shot 54
percent, becoming only the fourth Lakers opponent this season to
hit more than half of its field goals.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're just kind of closing down the season. It's hard not to
coast a little bit at this time of the year,'' coach Phil Jackson
said, noting the Lakers' withering magic number. ``It makes it hard
to keep pushing these guys to the limit. They have the confidence
to win and they know how to do the job, and yet we don't feel like
we're playing as well as we can.''
</P>
<P>
   But even a less-than-perfect win gave Jackson a chance to ease
up on Shaquille O'Neal, who played a mere 37 minutes, and in a
subdued performance, finished with 19 points, eight assists and a
four rebounds, matching his season low.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was chilling out tonight,'' O'Neal said. ``I was looking to
pass a lot and get everybody else involved. I didn't do too much on
the boards or point-wise, but my teammates, they stuck up for me.''
</P>
<P>
   Ron Harper scored 13 points and the Lakers got 12 apiece from
Rick Fox (starting in place of Rice) and A.C. Green, playing his
NBA record-extending 1,100th consecutive game.
</P>
<P>
   Milestones have come and gone quickly this season for the
Lakers, so the 60-win mark passed without much talk.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have a chance to maybe win 65 or maybe even win 70,''
O'Neal said, ``but our main goal is much higher than that. We just
want to do excellent and end up in the playoffs. We're just
preparing ourselves for that now.''
</P>
<P>
   That preparation will include resting O'Neal as much as
possible, resting the other starters and probably putting Harper on
the injured list. But first things first.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're just happy we got to 60 wins,'' Jackson said. ``There's
no doubt about the fact we're pleased that we were able to reach
that number. But the concept now is to eliminate Portland as
quickly as possible and move into a space where we can generate,
moderate the time and the effort by each player as he goes out and
plays every night and maintain kind of a level here until the end
of the season.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
