<P>
   COXNET LIFESTYLES _ (EDS: This is the CoxNet LIFESTYLES page for
the current week. This layout is now available.)
</P>
<P>
   COXNET LIFESTYLES 0330: SOFT SKIN -- There are three secrets to
glowing, healthy complexion, say skin-care experts _ moisturize,
moisturize, moisturize. And after months of cold air with low
humidity and superheated dry indoor air, your skin is ready for a
spring break and the need for moisture treatment. In an informal
test of drugstore vs. department store moisturizers, our four
testers split evenly with two preferring the less expensive brands
and two the pricey ones. (Johnson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
Art includes four 2-column color photos of women who tested the
lotions and four 2-column photos of the different brands of
lotions.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: CHEAP CHIC -- It's hard to miss the design revolution
taking place in the aisles of the nation's mass merchandisers.
Designer looks are coming to discount retailers. (Brooks, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) Art includes a 1-column color photo of a
chair, a 1-column color photo of a teakettle, a 1-column color
photo of a can opener and a 1-column color photo of a wall clock.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: CONSUMER Q&AMP;A -- How to get crayon marks off a freshly
painted wall and other answers to consumer-related questions.
(Greig, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
