collection of Japanese art outside Japan, now exhibited at the
Metropolitan Museum. By Roberta Smith.
</P>
<P>
   NY-JEWISH-MUSEUM (New York) _ The Jewish Museum has not flinched
from efforts to make the story of more than 3,000 years of Jewish
civilization viewer-friendly. And with an eye to enhancing and
streamlining the presentation, the museum has embarked on a
two-stage reinstallation. The first stage, dealing with the ancient
world and the early Diaspora is now open. The second stage, which
continues the story to the present, is to be completed by 2001. By
Grace Glueck.
</P>
