<P>
   FOUNDATION _ WASHINGTON _ Despite yesterday's report that
foundations are giving away more money than ever, community groups
say that it is misleading to think that there's a bigger pot of
money to divide. Most of the increase comes from large corporations
with specialized interests, said Rick McKelvey, vice president for
development at the Atlanta Symphony Orchestra. ``There is not this
plethora of new money out there,'' he said. ``Most communities are
working harder than ever for a smaller piece of the pie.'' (Carr,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
