<P>
   AUDITS _ WASHINGTON _ Only 13 of the federal government's 24
major agencies won a clean bill of health from auditors for their
1999 financial statements. Although that was one more success than
last year, the results fell well short of the Clinton
administration's goal. The Pentagon remains the biggest offender,
with auditors saying that it had insufficient records for $119
billion in property, plant and equipment. (Malone, Cox News
Service)
