   ALAMIN _ ATLANTA _ Evidence specialists will begin combing
through Jamil Al-Amin's Mercedes , looking for something that might
suggest a motive for the shooting of two Fulton deputies. They will
vacuum up every speck of dirt and fiber in the car and examine it
all. Most of what they find will be meaningless. But evidence of
contraband, such as guns, would be a big score. The car, the tag
found nearby, might also provide clues about others who might have
helped him in Alabama. (Warner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BUS-TRAIN _ TENNGA, Ga. _ Investigators began the tedious task
Thursday of recreating the train-school bus crash that killed three
children. Using a 1998 school bus matching the one hit Tuesday and
the same CSX locomotive involved in the accident, safety officals
spent the day making measurements to determine when driver Rhonda
Cloer should have been able to see and hear the oncoming train.
(Bennett, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
