<P>
   LUMINEX _ AUSTIN, Texas _ The first Austion biotech company to
go public raises $77 million in its IPO, the third local offering
in 2000. It goes at a risky time, after a very shaky day on the
Nasdaq Wednesday. (Cocks, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   COKE-LAWSUIT _ ATLANTA _ Following developments in the racial
discrimination case against Coca-Cola. The Rev. Jesse Jackson met
with Coke officials at the company's headquarters for a second day
Thursday in an effort to push a a quick settlement in the case.
(Unger, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HOMEDEPOT _ ATLANTA _ Home Depot named Mark Baker executive vice
president and chief operating officer, a post that's been left
vacant since President Arthur Blank became chief executive in 1997.
Baker, who was president of the Mid-South and Southern divisions,
has been with the home improvement retailer for four years. (Bond,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
