<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-APPLES-CHICAGO-ART-5THTAKE-NYT </SLUG>
 
CHICAGO: Well-chosen wines.  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Attractions
</P>
<P>
   ART INSTITUTE OF CHICAGO, 111 S. Michigan Ave., at (312)
443-3600. ``Monet to Moore,'' featuring works from the Sara Lee
collection, through May 29. ``Conserve a Legacy,'' through April
30. Admission: $8; $5 for the elderly and students; free, children
under 5 and on Tuesdays. Hours: Mondays through Fridays, 10 a.m. to
4:30 p.m.; Tuesdays to 8 p.m.; Saturdays and Sundays, 10 a.m. to 5
p.m.
</P>
<P>
   TERRA MUSEUM OF AMERICAN ART, 664 N. Michigan Ave., (312)
664-3939. ``Outsider and Folk Art from Chicago Collections,''
through May 28. ``The City and the Country: American Perspectives,
1870-1920,'' through May 7. Hours: Tuesdays, 10 a.m. to 8 p.m.
(free); Wednesdays through Saturdays, 10 a.m. to 6 p.m.; Sundays,
noon to 5 p.m. Admission: $7; $3.50, the elderly; children under 18
free.
</P>
<P>
   MUSEUM OF CONTEMPORARY ART, 220 E. Chicago Ave., (312) 280-2660.
``Alexander Calder in Focus''; ``Pierre Huyghe: Blanche Neige
Lucie'' and ``Drawing on the Figure,'' through June 25. Hours:
Tuesdays, 10 a.m. to 8 p.m.; Wednesdays through Sundays, 10 a.m. to
5 p.m. Admission: $7; $4.50, students and the elderly; free, under
12.
</P>
<P>
   LINCOLN PARK ZOO, 2200 N. Cannon Drive, at Lake Shore Drive and
Fullerton Parkway, (312) 742-2000. Daily, 9 a.m. to 6 p.m. Free.
Parking: $7.
</P>
<P>
   FIELD MUSEUM, Chicago's Museum Campus, Roosevelt Road at Lake
Shore Drive, (312) 922-9410. ``The Dead Sea Scrolls,'' through June
11. Reserved tickets: (312) 902-1500. ``Masks: Faces of Culture,''
through May 14. ``Sounds From the Vaults,'' through June 18. Daily,
9 a.m. to 5 p.m. Admission: $8; $4, children under 12, students and
the elderly. Free on Wednesdays. Supplement for ``Dead Sea
Scrolls'': $3; $2, children and the elderly.
</P>
<P>
   MUSEUM OF SCIENCE AND INDUSTRY, 57th Street and Lake Shore
Drive, (773) 684-1414. ``Titanic,'' through Sept. 4. Reservations:
www.msichicag.org. Daily, 9:30 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. Admission: $7; $6,
the elderly; $3.50, children 3 to 11. Supplement for ``Titanic'':
$10; $8, children and the elderly.
</P>
<P>
   JOHN G. SHEDD AQUARIUM, 1200 S. Lake Shore Drive, (312)
939-2438. ``Sea Horse Symphony,'' through summer. Hours: Weekdays,
9 a.m. to 5 p.m.; Saturdays and Sundays, 9 a.m. to 6 p.m.
Admission: $13; $9, children 3 to 11 and the elderly. Go early on
weekends.
</P>
<P>
   CHICAGO ARCHITECTURE FOUNDATION, 224 S. Michigan Ave., (312)
922-3432. Boat tours from April 29 through June 4, leaving from
Mercury Cruise Line dock, southwest corner of the Michigan Avenue
Bridge. Departures: Weekdays, 11 a.m., 1 p.m. and 3 p.m.; Saturdays
and Sundays, 11 a.m., noon, 1 p.m., 2 p.m. and 3 p.m. Tickets: $21.
Also walking tours; information available at number above.
</P>
<P>
   CHICAGO SYMPHONY ORCHESTRA, Symphony Center, Orchestra Hall, 220
S. Michigan Ave., (312) 294-3000. Works by Beethoven and
Takemitsu's ``From Me Flows What You Call Time,'' with the
percussion ensemble Nexus; Christoph Eschenbach conducts. Today at
1:30 p.m.; Saturday at 8 p.m.; Sunday at 3 p.m. Tickets: $23 to
$95.
</P>
<P>
   LYRIC OPERA, 20 N. Wacker Drive, at Madison Street, (312)
332-2244. Season begins on Sept. 23.
</P>
<P>
   JOFFREY BALLET, Auditorium Theater, 50 E. Congress Parkway,
(312) 902-1500. Season begins in the fall; June 8-11, performs at
the Ravina Festival in Highland Park; tickets, $15 to $30.
Information: (847) 266-5100.
</P>
<P>
   GOODMAN THEATER, 200 S. Columbus Drive, (312) 443-3800. ``Boy
Gets Girl'' by Rebecca Gilman. Friday night and Saturday night at
8; Sunday at 2 and 7:30 p.m. Through April 8. Tickets: $29 to $42.
``Schoolgirl Figure,'' by Wendy MacLeod. Friday night and Saturday
night at 8; Sunday at 2 and 7:30 p.m. Preview tickets: $18; after
April 10: $23 to $28. Through April 30.
</P>
<P>
   COURT THEATER, 5535 S. Ellis Av., (773) 753-4472. Rotating
repertory through May 28. Tonight and tomorrow night at 8 and
Sunday at 2:30 p.m., ``The Learned Ladies,'' by Moliere. Sunday at
7:30 p.m., ``Fair Ladies at a Game of Poem Cards,'' by Peter
Oswald. Tickets: $22 to $26.
</P>
<P>
   STEPPENWOLF THEATER, 1650 N. Halsted St., (312) 335-1650. Main
stage dark until April 6, when ``One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest''
opens, starring Gary Sinise and Amy Morton; directed by Terry
Kinney. Through June 18. Tickets: $32 to $52. Studio Theater: ``The
Infidel,'' by Bruce Norris, tonight at 7:30; tomorrow at 3 and 7:30
p.m.; Sunday at 3 p.m. Through April 9. Tickets: $18 to $22.
</P>
