<P>
   RAINIER-WOOD (Mount Rainier, Wash.) _ Joe Wood, a 34-year-old
New Yorker, a widely respected writer and editor, is presumed dead.
Last July, he decided to go bird-watching in Mount Rainier National
Park. Park rangers believe Wood either fell through snow to a creek
bed or died of exposure. Under different circumstances, the
rangers' assessment might have been accepted by grieving family
members. But Wood's disappearance is unlike any to precede it on a
mountain replete with disappearances.
</P>
<P>
   By Kimberly A.C. Wilson. (Story has moved in the ``a''
category.)
