 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-NJ-SENATE-CAMPAIGN-NYT (moved on Monday, March 27)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, March 27,
about the campaign of former Gov. Jim Florio for the Democrats'
Senate nomination in New Jersey misstated the pronunciation of the
surname of his opponent, Jon S. Corzine. (An article on Sept. 24,
1999, also included the error.) The pronunciation is COR-zyne, not
cor-ZYNE.
</P>
<P>
   BC-INTERACTIVE-AD-COLUMN-NYT (moved on Sunday, March 26)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, March 26,
about a merger between Red Sky Interactive and Nuforia Inc.
misidentified the agency that developed the Web site for Altoid
mints. It was Nuforia, not Red Sky.
</P>
