<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THERE'S NO PEOPLE LIKE SHOW PEOPLE
</HEADLINE>
  
 
 c.2000 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   W &UR; im Wenders &LR; , director of ``The Buena Vista Social Club,''
bolted from his seat and left when ``One Day in September'' took
the Oscar for best documentary feature.
</P>
<P>
   Fox411 says that the winner, which is about the massacre of
Israeli athletes at the Munich Olympics in 1972, doesn't have a
distributor and hasn't ever been released. ``The Buena Vista Social
Club'' has earned $10 million at the box office.
</P>
<P>
   All voters in the documentary category were required to see all
the nominees, which were shown one afternoon in Hollywood. ``But
who has time to see five films in the afternoon?'' said one voter.
``Old people, retired people, no one who'd be digging Cuban
music.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
_A recent New York benefit for the  &UR; Joseph Papp &LR;  Public Theater-New
York Shakespeare Festival honored  &UR; Mandy Patinkin &LR; , who took to the
stage and reminisced.
</P>
<P>
   Patinkin, reports the New York Observer, ``said he sang the
mourner's kaddish in Hebrew in memory of Papp's son,  &UR; Tony &LR; , who
succumbed to AIDS in 1991, just months before Papp would also die.
</P>
<P>
   ```Joe said that it was beautiful,''' said Patinkin, ```and that
he'd like me to do it tomorrow night for  &UR; Jackie Mason  &LR; and some
people.'''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
_ &UR; George Hamilton &LR; , who'll be opening with  &UR; Joan Collins  &LR; in ``Love
Letters'' next month, is  &LR; not  &LR; living with  &UR; Danielle Steel &LR; , his
frequent date (her bodyguard served as chaperon at the post-Oscar
parties).  &UR; Agnes Chen Brown &LR; , one of Hamilton's neighbors in a Nob
Hill apartment house, says he is the ``most polite celebrity'' she
has ever encountered.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; THE TROUBLE &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; WITH WINNING &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Alexandra Brichacek &LR; , who lives in San Jose and is soon to be
married, was one of 14 Bride's magazine contest winners, the prize
being free airfare from her hometown to Los Angeles, and the
opportunity to be an extra in ``The Wedding Planner'' with
 &UR; Jennifer Lopez &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   Turned out the free flight was on US Airways, which doesn't go
directly. ``In order to go from SFO to LAX,'' she writes, ``I would
have had to make a stopover in Pittsburgh, Pa., for a total of 12
hours flying time.'' Excited about the experience but unwilling to
spend all day flying, she decided to pay for her own flight, plus,
as the contract had stipulated, hotel and food for the two-day
trip, plus car rental.
</P>
<P>
   Brichacek says that fewer than five winners showed up. Like
extras on most movies, they sat around for a good deal of the day.
When the cameras rolled, Brichacek says, she and her fellow brides
were ``not even in the shot.''
</P>
<P>
   The trip cost the ``winner'' $450. ``I did see Jennifer Lopez,''
she writes, ``but was not allowed to take a picture. ... We never
got to meet the director or anybody affiliated with the movie.''
</P>
<P>
   ``That's what it's like to be an extra,'' says the magazine's
 &UR; Lauren Sueskind &LR; , noting that the contract had specified the
financial burdens to the borne by the winners. ``We gave her the
full experience.'' Brichacek is glad it was a once-in-a-lifetime
experience.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _``Bushisms'' and ``Gorespeak'' are drab terms, says  &UR; Bill &LR; 
 &UR; O'Hara &LR; , who suggests instead ``Bushquack'' and ``Gorble.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
_ &UR; Peter Tamases  &LR; wants to know why the California Department of
Motor Vehicles didn't waggle its censoring finger at a license
plate that began ``4CUE.''
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``The president gets off on the country. The junkie gets off on
a couple of hits. They're the same, both cut from the same cloth.
They're just men.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Whitney Houston &LR;  in Jane magazine.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service Clients) &QL;  &LR;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
