</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _``Bushisms'' and ``Gorespeak'' are drab terms, says  &UR; Bill &LR; 
 &UR; O'Hara &LR; , who suggests instead ``Bushquack'' and ``Gorble.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
_ &UR; Peter Tamases  &LR; wants to know why the California Department of
Motor Vehicles didn't waggle its censoring finger at a license
plate that began ``4CUE.''
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``The president gets off on the country. The junkie gets off on
a couple of hits. They're the same, both cut from the same cloth.
They're just men.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Whitney Houston &LR;  in Jane magazine.
