<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ERNESTMURRAY-COLUMN31-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Compared to Nyquil, gasoline is a bargain
 &HT;    By Ernest Murray
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   LUFKIN, Texas _ ``If you really think about it, we aren't paying
a whole lot for gasoline,'' read the e-mail I received the other
day. That's exactly what I've been saying all along.
</P>
<P>
   We've been spoiled for too long by gasoline prices that are
artificially low.
</P>
<P>
   Let the rest of the world deal with gasoline prices that are $2,
$3 and $4 a gallon, but let the price at the pump at the corner
convenience store go over a buck a gallon, and we all start
moaning.
</P>
<P>
   Good grief, not until the gas crisis of the '70s did anyone
consider that oil was definitely a finite resource. Back then, it
was hard to find gasoline at any price. Later, oil producers
increased production and gas prices fell. Now, they are on the way
up again. But one thing is for certain: at some point we'll either
be buying a syntectic fuel or we won't be driving.
</P>
<P>
   For comparison, the e-mail listed some prices per gallon for
other items that make gasoline almost a bargain, even at $1.50 a
gallon.
</P>
<P>
   _ Diet Snapple 16oz for $1.29 equals $10.32 per gallon.
</P>
<P>
   _ Lipton Ice Tea 16oz for $1.19 equals $ 9.52 per gallon.
</P>
<P>
   _ Gatorade 20oz for $1.59 equals $ 10.17 per gallon.
</P>
<P>
   _ Ocean Spray 16oz for $1.25 equals $ 10 per gallon.
</P>
<P>
   _ Pint of milk 16oz for $1.59 equals $12.72 per gallon.
</P>
<P>
   _ Brake fluid 12oz for $3.15 equals $ 33.60 per gallon.
</P>
<P>
   _ Evian water 9oz for $1.49 equals $ 21.19 per gallon.
</P>
<P>
   _ Pepto Bismol 4oz for $3.85 equals $123.20 per gallon.
</P>
<P>
   _ Whiteout 7oz for $1.39 equals $25.42 per gallon.
</P>
<P>
   _ Scope 1.5oz for $0.99 equals $ 84.48 per gallon.
</P>
<P>
   And the topper:
</P>
<P>
   _ Vick's Nyquil 6oz for $8.35 equals $ 178.13 per gallon.
</P>
<P>
   So next time you're at the pump, be glad your car doesn't run on
Nyquil, Scope or Whiteout.
</P>
<P>
   Ernest Murray is managing editor of The Lufkin Daily News.
E-mail: emurray(at)coxnews.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
